<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,696,2043]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">
<subSubSection box="[199,531,874,899]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" type="nomenclature">
<taxonomicName authority="(Girard, 1850)" authorityName="Girard" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Girard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[199,531,874,899]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Girardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seriata" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis box="[199,372,875,899]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Girardia tigrina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Girard, C. F." box="[385,524,874,898]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="264 - 265" refId="ref1608" refString="Girard, C. F. (1850) A brief account of the fresh water species of Planariae inhabiting the United States. Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History, 3, 264 - 265. [1848 - 1851]" type="journal article" year="1850">Girard, 1850</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="597" type="distribution">
have been recorded in thirteen countries so far. It is commonly accepted that this species is native to North America, where it is widely distributed, forming a polytypic group (
<bibRefCitation author="Kenk, R." box="[1116,1238,910,934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1 - 90" refId="ref1874" refString="Kenk, R. (1974) Index of the Genera and Species of the Freshwater Triclads (Turbellaria) of the World. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 183, 1 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.183" type="journal article" year="1974">Kenk 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kenk, R." box="[1249,1305,910,934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref1921" refString="Kenk, R. (1989) Revised list of the North American freshwater Planarians (Platyhelminthes: Tricladida: Paludicola). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 476, 1 - 10. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.476" type="journal article" year="1989">1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sluys, R. &amp; Joffe, B. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G." pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="642" refId="ref2189" refString="Sluys, R., Joffe, B. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1995) An alien flatworm in Australian waters. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 38, 642." type="journal article" year="1995">
Sluys 
<emphasis box="[1383,1437,910,934]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vila-Farre, M. &amp; Sluys, R. &amp; Almagro, I. &amp; Handberg-Thorsager, M. &amp; Romero, R." box="[218,449,946,970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1 - 57" refId="ref2466" refString="Vila-Farre, M., Sluys, R., Almagro, I., Handberg-Thorsager, M. &amp; Romero, R. (2011) Freshwater planarians (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida) from the Iberian Peninsula and Greece: diversity and notes on ecology. Zootaxa, 2779 (1), 1 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2779.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">
Vila-Farré 
<emphasis box="[333,387,946,970]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). In the 1920s, it was introduced in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Meinken, H." box="[917,1074,946,970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="94 - 96" refId="ref2019" refString="Meinken, H. (1925) Ein verkannter Laichrauber. Wochenschrift fur Aquarien und Terrarienkunde, 22, 94 - 96." type="journal article" year="1925">Meinken 1925</bibRefCitation>
) and after that it started to expand southwards and eastwards during the next decades reaching southern 
<collectingCountry box="[898,973,982,1005]" name="France" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1046,982,1006]" name="Spain" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Spain</collectingCountry>
(including the 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1383,982,1006]" country="Spain" name="Illes Baleares" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Balearic Islands</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,200,1017,1041]" name="Italy" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Italy</collectingCountry>
in the late 1960s to early 1970s (
<bibRefCitation author="Baguna, J. &amp; Salo, E. &amp; Romero, R." box="[567,779,1017,1042]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="15 - 30" refId="ref1508" refString="Baguna, J., Salo, E. &amp; Romero, R. (1980) Les planaries d'aigues dolces a Catalunya i les illes Balears. Butlleti de la Institucio Catalana d'Historia Natural, 45, 15 - 30." type="journal article" year="1980">
Baguñà 
<emphasis box="[658,714,1017,1041]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
1980
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gourbault, N." box="[791,964,1017,1041]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="3 - 7" refId="ref1652" refString="Gourbault, N. (1969) Expansion de Dugesia tigrina (Girard), planaire Americaine introduite en Europe. Annales de Limnologie, 5 (1), 3 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / limn / 1969006" type="journal article" year="1969">Gourbault 1969</bibRefCitation>
). There are also records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1292,1390,1017,1041]" name="Australia" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,212,1054,1077]" name="Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kawakatsu, M. &amp; Tamura, S. &amp; Takai, M. &amp; Yamamoto, K. &amp; Ueno, R. &amp; Oki, I." box="[226,469,1053,1077]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="5 - 11" refId="ref1797" refString="Kawakatsu, M., Tamura, S., Takai, M., Yamamoto, K., Ueno, R. &amp; Oki, I. (1993) The first record of occurence of a naturalized population of Dugesia tigrina (Girard, 1850) at Nagasaki, Kyushu, Japan (Turbellaria, Tricladida, Paludicola). Bulletin of the Biogeographical Society of Japan, 48, 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="1993">
Kawakatsu 
<emphasis box="[353,406,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sluys, R. &amp; Joffe, B. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G." box="[480,662,1053,1077]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="642" refId="ref2189" refString="Sluys, R., Joffe, B. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1995) An alien flatworm in Australian waters. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 38, 642." type="journal article" year="1995">
Sluys 
<emphasis box="[546,600,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamura, S. &amp; Oki, I. &amp; Kawakatsu, M. &amp; Ninagawa, M. &amp; Matsusato, T. &amp; Suzuki, H." box="[673,878,1053,1077]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="133 - 137" refId="ref2336" refString="Tamura, S., Oki, I., Kawakatsu, M., Ninagawa, M., Matsusato, T. &amp; Suzuki, H. (1985) A note on an introduced species of freshwater planarian, Dugesia tigrina (Girard, 1850), found in culture ponds of australian crayfish in Kagoshima prefecture, Japan. Bulletin of Fuji Women`s College, 23, 133 - 137." type="journal article" year="1985">
Tamura 
<emphasis box="[761,814,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,696,2043]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">
In this paper, we present the first record of this species in Eastern Europe. We identified morphologically freshwater planarians found in the Desna River (
<collectingCountry box="[564,653,1125,1149]" name="Ukraine" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
) as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Girard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[701,877,1125,1149]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Girardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seriata" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis box="[701,877,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Girardia tigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The identity of these planarians was subsequently confirmed by molecular analysis of 
<emphasis box="[536,775,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Cytochrome Oxidase I</emphasis>
gene (COI) sequences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
